stepTitle: An arrow is shot vertically upward at a rate of 220 feet per second. Use the projectile formula h $$=$$ $$-16t^2$$ + vt, to determine when height of the arrow will be 400 feet.
stepBody: Please enter your answer as a real number without a unit. If there is more than one answer, please enter it as (a,b) where $$a<b$$.
